AGI - The EU remains to look at and the President of the European Commission, Ursula von der Leyen announces that Brussels has prepared "a solid plan" with "solid countermeasures" to counteract <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-03-30/trump-dazi-chat-gate-groenland Donaldsp-30668711/"
In a speech to the European Parliament, Von der Leyen insisted that the main objective of the European Union is to find "a negotiated solution", but warned: "Europe has not begun this dispute. We do not necessarily want to take retaliation measures, but we have a solid plan to do so if necessary." &nbsp;
"If necessary, we will protect our interests, our people, our businesses. I want to be very clear about the objective of our response," said the President of the Community Executive, adding that "the conflict does not affect anyone". &nbsp;
Von der Leyen pointed out that <a href="https://www.agi.it/economic/news/2025-03-26/dazi-trump-auto-straniere-30621438/"> reciprocal duties of 25%></a> that Trump wants to apply "will be a nightmare for all US importers" and added that "no one today needs this: neither the United States". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"The duties are taxes that will pay people.» The duties are taxes for Americans on their foods and their drugs. The duties will only increase inflation. Exactly the opposite of what we want to achieve. US factories will pay more for the components produced in Europe. This will cost jobs," the German leader continued. &nbsp;
In this context, Von der Leyen assured that the trade flow > between the EU and the United States "is practically balanced" > and showed his willingness to work with Washington "on the trade balance, both of goods and services". &nbsp;
At the same time, he said that "Europe has many cards" to respond, from trade to technology, through the size of the single market and the diversification of trade relations with third countries. &nbsp;
The President of the Commission insisted that Brussels would conclude a trade agreement with India > - where he went to February - by the end of this year, in addition to intensifying negotiations with Indonesia and Thailand. &nbsp;>
He also recalled that both you and the President of the European Council, António Costa, will go to Samarkand > at the end of this week to participate in the first summit between the EU and Central Asia. &nbsp;
"When trust in multilateral institutions is under pressure and uncertainty is the norm, the European Union is a reliable and trusted partner," said Costa, at the same debate in the European Parliament. &nbsp;
Costa > stressed that "a multipolar world does not necessarily involve an unbridled competition", because "it also creates new strategic opportunities for collaboration > that we cannot afford to lose" and, in line with Von der Leyen, assured that "the EU is well prepared to exploit them". &nbsp;
Von der Leyen also announced that the Vice-President of the European Commission, Stéphane Séjourné, will present next month a plan to promote innovation in the Community market.
